OL,3,CWhy Criccieth holds a special place in
OL,4,CD-Day history
OL,6,FIt was in the North Wales town that
OL,7,Fthe members of the Kieffer commandos,
OL,8,Frifles in hand, took their first steps
OL,9,Fin getting back home towards the
OL,10,Finvasion of Normandy - and towards D-
OL,11,FDay.
OL,13,FHistorian Professor Merfyn Jones said
OL,14,Fthere's been a "kind of lapse of
OL,15,Fmemory" about the soldiers and it is
OL,16,Fonly now that people have recognised
OL,17,Fthem with a plaque in Criccieth.
