OL,3,CWhy Criccieth holds a special place in
OL,4,CD-Day history
OL,6,F"This was home to a very unique
OL,7,Fcompany of soldiers," he said. "They
OL,8,Fwere the marine commandos and they
OL,9,Flater had to honour of being the only
OL,10,FFrench troops that were involved in
OL,11,Fthe D-Day landing.
OL,13,F"So, they were a very particular breed
OL,14,Fof men. They are highly trained, very
OL,15,Ftough, very strong, and very
OL,16,Fdetermined to free France from the
OL,17,FNazis.
