OL,3,CWhy Criccieth holds a special place in
OL,4,CD-Day history
OL,6,F"It was the best place possible to
OL,7,Fpractice for a sea-borne invasion,
OL,8,Fwhich is what they had to do at 7.30
OL,9,Fon 6 June 1944. They had to jump into
OL,10,Fthe water in Normandy and attack some
OL,11,Fvery strong German oppositions."
OL,13,FBut many of the men did not live to
OL,14,Fsee the end of this day 80 years ago.
OL,16,FNow, a group based in Criccieth have
OL,17,Fcreated a knitted version the
OL,18,Fcommandos' story in order to keep it
OL,19,Falive as part of a huge project called
OL,20,Fthe Longest Yarn. They were even able
OL,21,Fto take their work to France.
